Package com.github.jeuxjeux20.orderedmultibinders

Annotation Type Order

@Inherited
@Target(TYPE)
@Retention(RUNTIME)
public @interface Order
Specifies the relative constraints on the position of bindings targeting this class in a Multibinder.
See Also:
OrderedMultibinders

  • Optional Element Summary

    Optional Elements 
    Modifier and Type Optional Element Description
    Class<?>[] after
    Returns the classes that this element should succeed.
    Class<?>[] before
    Returns the classes that this element should precede.
    int position
    Defines the position of the element when its exact position cannot be determined.

  • Element Details

    • before

      Returns the classes that this element should precede.

    • after

      Class<?>[] after
      Returns the classes that this element should succeed.
      Returns:
      the classes that this element should succeed
      Default:
      {}

    • position

      int position
      Defines the position of the element when its exact position cannot be determined.

      A higher value will put this element further in the list, while a lower value will put it closer.

      Note that a value of 0 is considered default and will get processed by a DefaultPositionProvider.

      Returns:
      the position of the element
      Default:
      0
